ent-PosterLegitCarbonDioxide-desc = This informational poster teaches the viewer what carbon dioxide is.

ent-PosterLegitDickGumshue-name = Dick Gumshue
ent-PosterLegitDickGumshue-desc = A poster advertising the escapades of Dick Gumshue, mouse detective. Encouraging crew to bring the might of justice down upon wire saboteurs.

ent-PosterLegitThereIsNoGasGiant-name = There Is No Gas Giant
ent-PosterLegitThereIsNoGasGiant-desc = Nanotrasen has issued posters, like this one, to all stations reminding them that rumours of a gas giant are false.

ent-PosterLegitJustAWeekAway-name = Just a Week Away...
ent-PosterLegitJustAWeekAway-desc = A poster advertising a long delayed project, it still claims it to be 'just a week away...'

ent-PosterLegitSecWatch-name = Sec is Watching You
ent-PosterLegitSecWatch-desc = A poster reminding you that security is watching your every move.

ent-PosterLegitAnatomyPoster-name = Anatomy of a spessman
ent-PosterLegitAnatomyPoster-desc = A poster showing the bits and bobs that makes you... you!

ent-PosterLegitMime-name = Mime Postmodern
ent-PosterLegitMime-desc = A postmodern depiction of a mime, superb!

ent-PosterLegitCarpMount-name = Wall-mounted Carp
ent-PosterLegitCarpMount-desc = Carpe diem!

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothDelam-name = Safety Moth - Delamination Safety Precautions
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothDelam-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to tell the viewer to hide in lockers when the Supermatter Crystal has delaminated, to prevent hallucinations. Evacuating might be a better strategy.

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothEpi-name = Safety Moth - Epinephrine
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothEpi-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to inform the viewer to help injured/deceased crewmen with their epinephrine injectors. "Prevent organ rot with this one simple trick!"

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothPiping-name = Safety Moth - Piping
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothPiping-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to tell atmospheric technicians correct types of piping to be used. "Pipes, not Pumps! Proper pipe placement prevents poor performance!"

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothMeth-name = Safety Moth - Methamphetamine
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothMeth-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to tell the viewer to seek CMO approval before cooking methamphetamine. "Stay close to the target temperature, and never go over!" ...You shouldn't ever be making this.

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothHardhat-name = Safety Moth - Hardhats
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothHardhat-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to tell the viewer to wear hardhats in cautious areas. "It's like a lamp for your head!"

ent-PosterLegitVacation-name = Nanotrasen Corporate Perks: Vacation
ent-PosterLegitVacation-desc = This informational poster provides information on some of the prizes available via the NT Corporate Perks program, including a two-week vacation for two on the resort world Idyllus.

ent-PosterLegitPeriodicTable-name = Periodic Table of the Elements
ent-PosterLegitPeriodicTable-desc = A periodic table of the elements, from Hydrogen to Oganesson, and everything inbetween.

ent-PosterLegitRenault-name = Renault Poster
ent-PosterLegitRenault-desc = Yap.

ent-PosterLegitNTTGC-name = Nanotrasen Tactical Game Cards
ent-PosterLegitNTTGC-desc = An advertisement for Nanotrasen's TCG cards: BUY MORE CARDS.

ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothSSD-name = Safety Moth - Space Sleep Disorder
ent-PosterLegitSafetyMothSSD-desc = This informational poster uses Safety Moth™ to tell the viewer about Space Sleep Disorder (SSD), a condition where the person stops reacting to things. "Treat SSD crew with care! They might wake up at any time!"

ent-PosterLegitOppenhopper-name = Oppenhopper
ent-PosterLegitOppenhopper-desc = A poster for a long-forgotten movie. It follows a group of tenacious greenhorns from the Grasshopper Sector as they defend against onslaughts of the infamous Nuclear Operatives. The tagline reads: "Nuke Ops will continue until robustness improves."

ent-PosterLegitTyrone-name = Tyrone's Guide to Space
ent-PosterLegitTyrone-desc = A poster advertising online schooling about space. The classes listed seem to cover things from the basic usage of station equipment to complicated subjects like creating pipebombs or covering entire hallways in spacelube. A disclaimer reads "It's never THAT bad, and at the end you might even get a tortilla."

ent-PosterLegitHelio-name = Helio Logistics ad
ent-PosterLegitHelio-desc = A poster advertising Helio Logistics and their adorable mascot. The slogan reads 'Come rain or shine, we deliver on time.'

ent-PosterMapBagel-name = Bagel Map
ent-PosterMapBagel-desc = A map of Bagel Station.

ent-PosterMapDelta-name = Delta Map
ent-PosterMapDelta-desc = A map of Delta Station.

ent-PosterMapMarathon-name = Marathon Map
ent-PosterMapMarathon-desc = A map of Marathon Station.

ent-PosterMapMoose-name = Moose Map
ent-PosterMapMoose-desc = A map of Moose Station.

ent-PosterMapPacked-name = Packed Map
ent-PosterMapPacked-desc = A map of Packed Station.

ent-PosterMapPillar-name = Pillar Map
ent-PosterMapPillar-desc = A map of NSS Pillar.

ent-PosterMapSaltern-name = Saltern Map
ent-PosterMapSaltern-desc = A map of Saltern Station.

ent-PosterMapSplit-name = Split Station Map
ent-PosterMapSplit-desc = A map of Split Station.

ent-PosterMapLighthouse-name = Lighthouse Map
ent-PosterMapLighthouse-desc = A map of Lighthouse.

ent-PosterMapWaystation-name = Waystation Map
ent-PosterMapWaystation-desc = A map of Waystation... wait isn't this packed upside down?

